A cop who set up a hidden camera to video the town police chief having sex in a public ambulance lost his job on Friday, while his boss kept his.

New Mexico officer Joshua Terrell tried to catch Jal police chief Larry Burns having sex inside and up against an ambulance on city property because he wanted to sabotage his run for magistrate.

Despite catching Burns on camera with a woman while wearing his gun and badge, the dastardly plan came back to haunt Terrell after he gave the footage to local television instead of Jal city manager, Bob Gallagher.

