'It would have been very easy if he had just come in with the tape and said, 'Mr Gallagher, I think something is going wrong in the department'.'

Gallagher said that Burns did make an error of judgement, but that no evidence could be found that he committed a crime or was even on duty when the tape was filmed.

The police chief, Larry Burns, also serves as the town of Jal’s Emergency Medical Services Director.

'In this case there was no criminal activity whatsoever, there was no proof whatsoever that it was on duty when he should have been working, ' said Gallagher according to Opposing Views.

'I think it was lapse of judgment. Something that I don’t think will keep him from being able to perform his duties when he comes back.'

